        public List<Object> getValuesAsObject()

      • getValueAsObject

        public Object getValueAsObject()
        Converts the first internally stored stringified value to a native Java object such as String, Calendar, Boolean, Long, Double, BigDecimal and BinaryValue based on the getType() value of this content property. Or returns null if there's no value.
        Returns:
        converted native Java object from the first internal stringified value based on content property type. Null if there's no value.
